    <info>
        <title>Dynamics</title>
    </info>
    <para>Dynamics are aligned with respect to the note to which they are applied. Therefore, if you
        are writing a chord with some dynamics marking, you should write that marking just after the
        first (lowest) note of the chord.</para>
    <informaltable>
        <tgroup cols="2">
            <colspec colnum="1" colname="col1"/>
            <colspec colnum="2" colname="col2"/>
            <tbody>
                <row>
                    <entry>pianississimo</entry>
                    <entry>***</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>pianissimo</entry>
                    <entry>**</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>piano</entry>
                    <entry>*</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>mezzo piano</entry>
                    <entry>*+</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>mezzo forte</entry>
                    <entry>+*</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>forte</entry>
                    <entry>+</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>fortissimo</entry>
                    <entry>++</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>fortississimo</entry>
                    <entry>+++</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>sforzando</entry>
                    <entry>**+ <emphasis role="italic">or</emphasis> ++*</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
